'''Barada TV''' is a [[London]]-based [[Syrian]] opposition satellite television network. Classified U.S. diplomatic cables, provided by the anti-secrecy Web site [[WikiLeaks]], show that the U.S. State Department has funneled $6 million to Barada TV between 2006 and 2011 to operate the satellite channel and finance other activities inside Syria, ''[[The Washington Post]]'' reported. The State Department refused to comment on this allegation.<ref>{{cite news|title=U.S. secretly backed Syrian opposition groups, cables released by WikiLeaks show|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/us-secretly-backed-syrian-opposition-groups-cables-released-by-wikileaks-show/2011/04/14/AF1p9hwD_story.html|publisher=TheWashingtonPost | first=Craig|last=Whitlock|date=18 April 2011| accessdate=18 July 2014}}</ref><ref>[http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2011/04/17/us-syria-opposition_n_850302.html "U.S. Secretly Backed Syrian Opposition Groups, Cables Released By WikiLeaks Show"], Huffington Post. April 17, 2011. Accessed April 17, 2011.</ref>

