'''Myawaddy(MWD)''' ({{lang-my|ျမ၀တီ}}) is a [[Myanmar]] [[Tatmadaw|military]]-owned television network based in [[Yangon]] and [[Naypyitaw]], [[Myanmar]]. It was launched on the 27 March 1995, in commemoration of the [[Armed Forces Day#Myanmar|Burmese Armed Forces Day]]. Its programming is also broadcast over the [[AsiaSat 2]] satellite. The average duration of broadcast is daily from 6 am to 11:30 pm.{{citation needed|date=March 2010}}

